            ContentJson = """{"appRoute":"/inventory/home/kiosk","startButtonLabel":"Tour Inventory Home","steps":[{"element":".inv-home__hero","popover":{"title":"Inventory Home","description":"This is where Inventory opens by default — a friendly, low-friction landing built for the shop floor. The title and subtitle tell you where you are; everything below works over the same data as the detailed warehouse view.","side":"bottom"}},{"element":".inv-home__manage","popover":{"title":"Manage Inventory","description":"Need the full warehouse model — bins, locations, movements, cycle counts, reservations, replenishment? This link in the top-right takes you to the detailed power view at /inventory/stock. Home and the detailed view share the same stock; this is just the door to the advanced tools.","side":"left"}},{"element":".tab-bar","popover":{"title":"Three Tabs","description":"Home has three views: Kiosk (big-button, one action at a time — the default), Tasks (search + a working list of parts with inline actions), and Dashboard (at-a-glance totals and the low-stock list). The active tab is part of the URL, so you can bookmark a direct link to any of them.","side":"bottom"}},{"element":".tab:nth-child(1)","popover":{"title":"Kiosk Tab","description":"The Kiosk tab — where you are now — is the tap-and-go view, ideal for a wall-mounted tablet. It shows four large buttons for the friendly stock verbs and nothing else, so there's no hunting for the right control.","side":"bottom"}},{"element":".inv-home__hint","popover":{"title":"One Action at a Time","description":"The hint reminds you that Kiosk is built for single, focused actions. Tap a verb, fill the small dialog, and you're done — the change is recorded instantly with a confirmation.","side":"bottom"}},{"element":"app-quick-action-panel","popover":{"title":"The Stock Verbs","description":"Four plain-language actions: Receive (stock came in — also captures a lot number), Use (stock went out), Count (set the true on-hand quantity after a physical count), and Find (look up a part — this one jumps you to the Tasks tab to search). Receive, Use, and Count each open a quick dialog: pick the part, enter a quantity, optionally a location and reason, then confirm.","side":"top"}},{"element":".tab:nth-child(2)","popover":{"title":"Tasks Tab","description":"Switch here for a working list: a search box, the same verb buttons, a low-stock warning strip, and a table of parts with on-hand quantities. Each row has inline Receive and Use buttons so you can act on a specific part without retyping its number.","side":"bottom"}},{"element":".tab:nth-child(3)","popover":{"title":"Dashboard Tab","description":"The Dashboard shows at-a-glance numbers — total parts, total units on hand, and a low-stock count that turns amber when anything is low — followed by the full low-stock list with a Receive shortcut on each line. Use it for a quick health check of your stock.","side":"bottom"}}]}"""
